{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Wire store-wide overlap step into _run_plan_review (LLM-gated, graceful skip, advisory) + ADR\n\n## Why\nThe overlap check fires in the tolerant window before claim â€” during plan review â€” folding results into the output as advisory coaching, WITHOUT ever blocking the claim or altering the claim-gate verdict. This is the integration seam tying enrichment + retrieval + judge into the workflow, and it delivers the epic's ADR.\n\n## What\n- Integrate in `_run_plan_review` (`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py:401` â€” the real post-pass site where rising-floor/completion-floor/sidecar/signing run; NOT the wrapper `review_plan` at :352). Overlap findings go in a SEPARATE `overlap[]` verdict key, EXCLUDED from the advisory cap and from the signed `coverage['counts']` â€” so the â‰¤3 overlap items never displace real plan-review advisories and the attestation is byte-identical whether overlap is on or off. (This resolves the earlier \"inject before counts are baked\" tension: we do NOT touch the baked counts at all.)\n- Steps: synchronously extract the query ticket's digest by calling S1's `enrich` on the plan-review orchestrator's already-assembled ticket context (the same whole-ticket text `_run_plan_review` passed to its own passes â€” title+description+comments), so no extra store read is needed, run `retrieve` (S5), run the pairwise `judge` (S6) â€” the no-embeddings retrieval is justified by the epic's recall experiment (digest-BM25F recall@20 = 1.0), so no embedding index is needed; attach â‰¤3 results to `overlap[]`. This injection happens AFTER `sidecar.emit()` and the attestation signing, so `overlap[]` is never part of the signed sidecar/coverage (reinforcing verdict-unchanged). Each item is exactly S6's surfaced-finding shape: `{counterpart_id: str, relation: \"duplicates\"|\"supersedes\"|\"depends_on\", shared_artifact: str, confidence: number, link_command: str}`. Whether a candidate is 'overlapping enough' to appear is decided ENTIRELY by S6's aggregation rule (both orderings agree + cited artifact + â‰Ąoverlap_conf_threshold); S7 does no thresholding of its own.\n- **CLI:** update `_render_plan_review_text` (`src/rebar/_cli/_llm_commands.py:386`) to print the `overlap[]` section.\n- **MCP:** the `review_plan` MCP tool is `NO_SCHEMA_EXEMPT` (returns a plain dict, no `outputSchema`, per `_mcp_llm.py:174` / `schemas/__init__.py:110`) â€” so there is NO output schema to update; `overlap[]` simply rides in the returned dict. (Corrects the earlier plan text.)\n- **Gate/skip:** if `[agents]`, plan-review, or the API key is absent â†’ silent no-op (no `overlap[]`, no error, claim proceeds). Runtime failure in S1/S5/S6 (exception, timeout, empty candidates) â†’ caught, empty `overlap[]`, logged, never blocks.\n- **Config flag:** `overlap_enabled` (default OFF) â€” a BOOL on the `VerifyConfig` dataclass (`src/rebar/_config_schema.py`, `[tool.rebar][verify]`, alongside `require_plan_review_for_claim`) WITH its companion entry in `_SECTIONS[\"verify\"]` (`= _as_bool`) â€” omitting the `_SECTIONS` entry silently drops the key. (`overlap_enabled` is the ONLY overlap key in `VerifyConfig`; all tunables live on `LLMConfig` per the other stories.)\n- **ADR:** write `docs/adr/0037-cross-ticket-overlap.md` capturing Cupid-digest-without-embeddings (+ the recall/latency/cost experiment evidence), event-store-as-enrichment-queue, digest-as-REVIEW_RESULT-sidecar, and overlap-at-review-time-not-as-a-5fd2-criterion. This is the epic's ADR deliverable.\n\n## Dependencies\nS1 (enrich), S5 (retrieve), S6 (judge). Sequenced LAST. NOTE: S3 also edits `plan_review/__init__.py` (the certification/enqueue path); this story edits `_run_plan_review` (a different function) â€” S7 lands after S3 to avoid a merge conflict (depends_on S3).\n\n## Scope\n- Edits: `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py` (`_run_plan_review` injection), `src/rebar/_cli/_llm_commands.py` (`_render_plan_review_text`), `src/rebar/_config_schema.py` (`VerifyConfig.overlap_enabled` + `_SECTIONS[\"verify\"]` entry), `docs/adr/0037-cross-ticket-overlap.md`.\n- **NO schema edit** (resolves the earlier contradiction): `overlap[]` rides in the returned plan-review dict WITHOUT touching `src/rebar/schemas/plan_review_verdict.schema.json`, which already declares `\"additionalProperties\": true` (verified) â€” so the extra `overlap` key validates without a schema change, and the MCP tool is `NO_SCHEMA_EXEMPT` anyway. Do NOT add `overlap[]` to the schema file; `test_verdict_schema_accepts_overlap` asserts a verdict dict carrying `overlap[]` still validates against the UNCHANGED `plan_review_verdict` schema.\n- OUT: component ops (S1/S5/S6), async enrichment (S2/S3/S4).\n\n## Testing\n- `tests/unit/test_plan_review_overlap.py` (FakeRunner + fixture corpus): `test_surfaced` (â‰¤3 in `overlap[]` with link commands); `test_verdict_unchanged` (signed coverage/attestation byte-identical vs overlap-off); `test_query_digest_at_review_time` (digest built from current full text, corpus-independent); `test_graceful_skip` ([agents]/key absent â†’ no `overlap[]`, verdict identical); `test_runtime_error` (judge raises â†’ empty `overlap[]`, no block); `test_flag_off` (`overlap_enabled=off` â†’ skipped); `test_render` (`overlap[]` in CLI text + MCP dict).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `review_plan` returns â‰¤3 findings in a dedicated `overlap[]` key (each with a `rebar link` command); claim NEVER blocked; signed coverage/attestation byte-identical to overlap-off; `pytest ...::{test_surfaced,test_verdict_unchanged}`.\n- [ ] Query digest generated at review time from current full text, independent of the enriched corpus; `::test_query_digest_at_review_time`.\n- [ ] `[agents]`/plan-review/key absent â†’ silent no-op, verdict identical; runtime S1/S5/S6 failure â†’ empty `overlap[]`, logged, never blocks; `::{test_graceful_skip,test_runtime_error}`.\n- [ ] `overlap_enabled` (bool, default OFF) on `VerifyConfig` WITH its `_SECTIONS[\"verify\"]` coercer gates the step; `::test_flag_off`. `overlap[]` rendered in CLI text and present in the MCP dict (no schema change â€” tool is NO_SCHEMA_EXEMPT); `::test_render`.\n- [ ] The ADR `docs/adr/0037-cross-ticket-overlap.md` is written (epic's ADR deliverable), citing the concrete experiment figures (recall@20 = 1.0, single-query 0.69 ms @ 800 digests, ~$1.90 one-time enrichment for 793 tickets) from the epic's experiment comment."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783648618849785001,"uuid":"2753b3c6-93ca-46d3-b569-5ab5d4c51460"}